## 1. Examine and specify the variable(s) {.smaller}

We will compare mouse $weight$ by $sex$.

$weight$ is the *response variable*

$sex$ is the *explanatory variable*

$y$ \~ $x$

$weight$ \~ $sex$


::: {.cell output-location='column-fragment'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggdensity(
  data = b,
  color = "sex",
  x = "weight",
  add = "mean",
  rug = TRUE
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](slides-12_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::


------------------------------------------------------------------------

I want the response variable on the $y$ axis and the explanatory variable on the $x$ axis.

Violin plot


::: {.cell output-location='column-fragment'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggviolin(
  data = b,
  y = "weight",
  x = "sex",
  fill = "sex",
  add = "mean_sd"
)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](slides-12_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::


